President-elect Joe Biden and Vice President-elect Kamala Harris will take the oath of office on the steps of the US Capitol on January 20, 2020.President Trump plans to leave Washington on the morning of Biden’s swearing-in, becoming the first modern-day president to skip his successor’s inauguration. His VP, Mike Pence, said he will attend Biden’s ceremony.  Experts says Biden will be tied to domestic policy because that is where the chaos began. Biden has stressed the need to unite the country after President Donald Trump's chaotic four years in office. Outgoing US leader, who refused to accept his defeat for more than two months, never congratulated Biden on his victory. Donald Trump will snub Biden by not attending the inauguration ceremony.